Implement the interactive file staging interface used by `chipper done`.

When chipper done is run, before committing, present the user with an ncurses-style
interface showing all changed and new files in the working tree.

Behavior:
- List all changed/new files with their status (modified, new, deleted)
- If any large binary files are present that were not previously committed, prompt
  to include or ignore them before entering the staging interface
- Allow the user to stage or unstage individual files
- Show a proposed commit message and allow the user to edit it
- On confirmation, commit the staged files with the final message

This interface is only used during `chipper done`. It gives the user full control
over what goes into the closing commit without requiring knowledge of raw git commands.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, git-integration
